What you need to know:

Algeria, who also play Equatorial Guinea and the Ivory Coast in Group E, may be among the favourites but Belmadi believes his team can thrive under pressure. “We just have to get on with the pressure," said the 45-year-old."Of course there is a difference between the situation in 2019 and now as we come into the tournament as the holders. But it's fine. We are ambitious and will do everything to fulfil our objective."